                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 Mumbai, Aug. 6 (PTI): Former Union minister Shashi Tharoor has apparently acknowledged that Sunanda Pushkar is his fiance. Tharoor, in Mumbai to deliver a lecture, was asked by the organisers if he had brought any visual aid. Yes. My fiance Sunanda, said Tharoor, according to a tweet by industrialist Anand Mahindra.           
	Tharoor and Pushkar recently visited temples in Maharashtra and performed puja together, sparking a buzz that they would soon marry.                  
	Ahmedabad: Gujarat High Court today granted the CBI two-day custody of former minister Amit Shah in the Sohrabuddin fake encounter case, setting aside a lower court order. The former minister of state for home will be in CBI remand for two days from Saturday. Shah, a confidant of chief minister Narendra Modi, is being held in Sabarmati Jail since his arrest on July 25.                   
	New Delhi (PTI): The rail coach factory at Rae Bareli, Uttar Pradesh, and a wheel manufacturing plant at Chapra, Bihar, will be completed in next the two years, railway minister Mamata Banerjee informed Rajya Sabha on Friday.                  
	Panaji (PTI): The Goa Assembly was rocked again by the issue of a police-drug peddler nexus on the last day of the monsoon session on Friday. The House was adjourned for an hour in the morning over state home minister Ravi Naiks statement alleging politicians who were in peddlers pay were persecuting him and his son.                  
	Madurai (PTI): Police have seized 194kg of unaccounted silver bars during intensified vehicle checks as part of security drills ahead of Independence Day celebration.                                                                                                                                              
